Based on previous reports, the CNT-Si structure can be considered as a Schottky junction, in which CNT membrane serves as metallic materials while silicon wafer serves as a semiconductor [8, 11, 15]. Figure 3 is the corresponding energy band diagram for CNT-SiNW junction. In this diagram, the barrier height (ΦB) is equal to the work function difference between CNT membranes and silicon nanowire; the equation for the barrier height [18] isFig. 3
